[color=#ffff00][size=3]install[/size][/color]

[size=3][color=#6d9eeb]for ece users:[/color] just put the file "_5_commonTriRaces.slot" in the CME_save folder
then go to the game, open showracemenu (i recommand this mod ([url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/33968/?]lossless race change[/url])
take nord race and choose the slot 5
DONE!

[color=#6d9eeb]for non ece users:[/color] when you install enhanced character edit for the first time, you need to run the game at least once!
this create the CME_save folder located in your saves folder then [/size][size=3]put the file "_5_commonTriRaces.slot" in the CME_save folder
then go to the game, open showracemenu (i recommand this mod ([url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/33968/?]lossless race change[/url])
[size=3]take nord race[/size] and choose the slot 5
DONE!

[color=#ffff00][size=3]for racemenu users just install with your favorite mods manager[/size][/color], in game choose breton race and activate the preset
[/size][size=3]DONE![/size]

[url=http://imgur.com/ggKLPUJ][img]http://i.imgur.com/ggKLPUJ.jpg[/img][/url]



[color=#e06666][size=3]it may be that this does not give the same result with your skyrim, depending on the mods you have installed, an example: if you have more hair/eyes mods installed, when you would load the preset it will not necessarily the same hair/eyes.[/size][/color][size=3]

[/size][size=3][/size][color=#e06666][size=3]also other textures can alter the appearance, you are warned  ;)[/size]
[/color][color=#e06666][/color]
[color=#ff0000][size=5]remember that this is only a preset so you can edit it at your convenience!!
you do not like it at all? too bad for you :/[/size][/color][color=#ff0000][size=5]
